President Biden has declared a major disaster in Wyoming due to flooding that occurred on June 15, 2023. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, particularly in Natrona County. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and statewide hazard mitigation measures. Jon K. Huss of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.